      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EVEN FLOW (8) goes very well at the distance with two wins and a placing from five starts. Comes off a (22.70) win last time, scoring by half a length in a Novice race over 400m at this track. Makes strong appeal on best. POTENT CREW (1) held her own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only a neck (22.92) behind Kaadadjan at this track. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Bold showing expected. GLOBAL FLASH (2) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 5 lengths at this track in a handy 22.72 beating Cool Ash. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Deserves serious consideration again. FLETCHER KEEPING (7) cannot be overlooked following a recent top-three finish in impressive time.",
